  "text": "Entanglement entropy is defined as follows -consider a density matrix ρ corresponding to a pure state defined on a Cauchy surface Σ. Let us partition Σ into two subregions A andĀ. For local quantum field theories, we expect the Hilbert space H Σ to factorize into the tensor product H Σ = H A ⊗ HĀ. If this is the case, we can trace over HĀ to obtain the reduced density matrix ρ A = Tr HĀ (ρ) [CITATION_1] which contains all the relevant information pertaining to the subregion A. Then the entanglement entropy between A andĀ is defined as the von Neumann entropy of ρ A",
